Actually I found this issue in CONNECT 4.2. As I did not find this version in the affected versions drop down list while creating this ticket, I am logging this against 4.1.

Validation suite can not pass by default. Even though MySQL drivers are correctly installed and loaded in SOAP UI, for some tests, which work with database directly (an example is *Patient Discovery* test in *g0* suite, whic fails in the first step - *clear correlations table* but there's more), we receive error: 

{{An error occured [No suitable driver found for jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/patientcorrelationdb], see error log for details.}}

I found the fix for this issue on SOAP UI [Tips & Tricks|http://www.soapui.org/Scripting-Properties/tips-a-tricks.html] page ([step 10|http://www.soapui.org/Scripting-Properties/tips-a-tricks.html#10-use-a-jdbc-driver-from-inside-a-groovy-script]) - basically adding

{code:java}com.eviware.soapui.support.GroovyUtils.registerJdbcDriver( "com.mysql.jdbc.Driver" ){code}

in the *setup script* for both *g0* and *g1* did the trick. This fix could be possibly place on more convenient place but the point is that CONNECT Validation Suite doesn't work out of the box and should be fixed then.
